en_127558_0	Brazil Police arrested the vice president of Facebook in Latin America, when he refused to share WhatsApp data.
en_127558_1	Diego Dzodan was thus arrested after he repeatedly refused to comply with court orders to hand over data for use in a criminal investigation into drugs trafficking, police said.
en_127558_2	Judge Marcel Maia Montalvao had in two previous instances issued fines against Facebook for refusing to release WhatsApp data, reports say.
en_127558_3	The information was needed as part "secrete judicial investigations involving organised crime and drug trafficking," he has said.
en_127558_4	Meanwhile, in a statement Facebook called Mr Dzodan's arrest an "extreme and disproportionate measure" and "Facebook has always been and will be available to address any questions Brazilian authorities may have," it added.
